Title: 1. Butch Cassidy and the Sundance Kid
Description: In 1890s Wyoming, Butch Cassidy and The Sundance Kid lead a band of outlaws. When a train robbery goes wrong, they find themselves on the run with a posse hard on their heels..

Title: 2. The Love Bug
Description: Down-on-his-luck race car driver Jim Douglas teams up with a little VW Bug that has a mind of it's own, not realizing Herbie's worth until a sneaky rival plots to steal him.

Title: 3. Midnight Cowboy
Description: A naive hustler travels from Texas to New York City to seek personal fortune, finding a new friend in the process.

Title: 4. On Her Majesty's Secret Service
Description: British agent James Bond goes undercover to pursue the villainous Ernst Stavro Blofeld, who is planning to hold the world to ransom.

Title: 5. Paint Your Wagon
Description: Two unlikely prospector partners share the same wife in a California gold rush mining town.

Title: 6. Satyricon
Description: A series of disjointed mythical tales set in first-century Rome.

Title: 7. Army of Shadows
Description: An account of underground resistance fighters in Nazi-occupied France.

Title: 8. The Wild Bunch
Description: An aging group of outlaws in 1913 Texas look for one last big score, selling stolen Army rifles to a rogue Mexican general during that country's revolution, as the traditional American West is disappearing around them.

Title: 9. Hello, Dolly!
Description: Matchmaker Dolly Levi travels to Yonkers to find a partner for "half-a-millionaire" Horace Vandergelder, convincing his niece, his niece's intended, and his two clerks to travel to New York City along the way.

Title: 10. True Grit
Description: A drunken, hard-nosed U.S. Marshal and a Texas Ranger help a stubborn teenager track down her father's murderer in Indian Territory.

Title: 11. The Swimming Pool
Description: Jean-Paul and Marianne spend lazy holidays at their villa in idyllic Southern France. However when Harry and his attractive young daughter Penelope show up, the dreamy summer days are suddenly filled with unspoken tension and jealousy.

Title: 12. Easy Rider
Description: Two bikers head from L.A. to New Orleans through the open country and desert lands, and along the way they meet a man who bridges a counter-culture gap of which they had been unaware.

Title: 13. Z
Description: The public murder of a prominent politician and doctor amid a violent demonstration is covered up by military and government officials. A tenacious magistrate is determined not to let them get away with it.

Title: 14. Mississippi Mermaid
Description: A wealthy plantation owner is captivated by a mysterious woman with a shady past.

Title: 15. Float Like a Butterfly, Sting Like a Bee
Description: He's the greatest fighter of all time. A sports icon that is loved throughout the world. A man driven by his ambition to be the best. Muhammad Ali is a name that to this day puts fear in the strongest of men. Hear from the people who knew him best, from experts of the world of boxing, relive the legendary fights and explore the life of boxing's greatest symbol, Ali.

Title: 16. The Sorrow and the Pity
Description: An in-depth exploration of the various reactions by the French people to the Vichy government's acceptance of the German invasion.

Title: 17. Duet for Cannibals
Description: About a secretary who is subjected to a power game by his new employer, an exiled former revolutionary leader and his wife.

Title: 18. Katzelmacher
Description: Jorgos, a migrant worker from Greece, joins a group of young people in Munich usually hanging around. This foreigner incites hostility and jealousy among them, and he is insulted as a "Communist" and "Greek dog". After having been attacked, Jorgos talks to Maria of his wish to return home.

Title: 19. Love Is Colder Than Death
Description: A small-time pimp is torn between his lover and Bruno the gangster.

Title: 20. The Italian Job
Description: A comic caper movie about a plan to steal a gold shipment from the streets of Turin by creating a traffic jam.

Title: 21. Age of Consent
Description: A grizzled Australian painter decides to jolt his stale creativity by moving to a remote island on the Great Barrier Reef, where he takes on an alluring, uninhibited young woman as his muse.

Title: 22. Women in Love
Description: Two best friends fall in love with a pair of women, but the relationships soon go in very different directions.

Title: 23. The Color of Pomegranates
Description: The life of the Armenian poet Sayat-Nova, from childhood to death: his spiritual journey, artistic endeavors, and inner conflicts within the cultural and historical context of Armenia. Hailed as revolutionary by Mikhail Vartanov.

Title: 24. The Prime of Miss Jean Brodie
Description: Eccentric and well-meaning teacher Jean Brodie's extravagantly romantic ideas about life and love overly impress her young pupils in 1930s Edinburgh, bringing her into direct conflict with her school's conservative headmistress.

Title: 25. The Gypsy Moths
Description: Three skydivers and their travelling thrill show barnstorm through a small midwestern town one Fourth of July weekend.

Title: 26. Marquis de Sade's Justine
Description: Penniless and separated from her sister, a beautiful, chaste orphan must endure an endless parade of villains, perverts and degenerates who covet her virtue and life.

Title: 27. They Shoot Horses, Don't They?
Description: The lives of a disparate group of contestants intertwine in a grueling and inhumane dance marathon.

Title: 28. Sam Whiskey
Description: A widow hires an ex-gambler to retrieve gold bars from a sunken river boat in Colorado and discreetly return them to the Federal Mint, from where they had been stolen by her dead husband.

Title: 29. Battle of Britain
Description: In 1940, the British Royal Air Force fights a desperate battle to prevent the Luftwaffe from gaining air superiority over the English Channel as a prelude to a possible Axis invasion of the U.K.

Title: 30. Kes
Description: A working-class English boy spends his free time caring for and training his pet kestrel.

Title: 31. Cactus Flower
Description: A dentist pretends to be married to avoid commitment, but when he falls for his girlfriend and proposes, he must recruit his lovelorn nurse to pose as his wife.

Title: 32. Support Your Local Sheriff!
Description: In the old west, a man becomes a Sheriff just for the pay, figuring he can decamp if things get tough. In the end, he uses ingenuity instead.

Title: 33. Freedom to Love
Description: Documentary, dramatized at times, on human sexual behaviour. Daring for its time for its approach to some of the most delicate aspects of this taboo subject.

Title: 34. Paranoia
Description: A rich, alcoholic widow assuages her loneliness through a ménage à trois with two seductive step-siblings, whose true motives threaten her sanity and life.

Title: 35. Topaz
Description: French Intelligence Agent Andre Devereaux becomes embroiled in Cold War politics, first by uncovering the events leading up to the 1962 Cuban Missile Crisis, and then breaking up an international Russian spy ring.

Title: 36. Bob & Carol & Ted & Alice
Description: Trendy West Coasters Bob and Carol are determined to embrace complete openness after a weekend of emotional honesty at a retreat.

Title: 37. The Damned
Description: The dramatic collapse of a wealthy, industrialist/Junker family during the reign of the Third Reich.

Title: 38. Guns of the Magnificent Seven
Description: Gunslinger Chris Adams is hired by a Mexican revolutionary to organize the rescue of his cause's leader from a brutal Army prison.

Title: 39. Sweet Charity
Description: Taxi dancer Charity continues to have faith in the human race despite endless disappointments at its hands, and hopes to finally meet the man to romance her away from her sleazy life. Just maybe, handsome Oscar will be the one to do it.

Title: 40. Eye of the Cat
Description: A man and his girlfriend plan to rob the mansion of the man's eccentric but wealthy aunt. However, the aunt keeps dozens of cats in her home, and the man is deathly afraid of cats.

Title: 41. The Assassination Bureau
Description: A woman causes a group of assassins to face their greatest challenge.

Title: 42. Last Summer
Description: During summer vacation on Fire Island, three young people become very close. When an uncool girl tries to infiltrate the trio's newly found relationship, they construct an elaborate plot that has violent results.

Title: 43. Play Dirty
Description: During World War II a group of British commandos in North Africa disguised as Italian soldiers must travel behind enemy lines and destroy a vital German oil depot.

Title: 44. Mackenna's Gold
Description: A bandit kidnaps a Marshal who has seen a map showing a gold vein on Indian lands, but other groups are looking for it too, while the Apache try to keep the secret location undisturbed.

Title: 45. Carry on Camping
Description: Sid and Bernie plan a camping trip with girlfriends Joan and Anthea, hoping to visit a nudist camp. They stumble upon a bizarre group of campers, including sex-starved schoolgirls and hippie bands, leading to hilarious misadventures.

Title: 46. The Magic Christian
Description: The world's richest man and his adopted hobo son set out to test the limits of human vanity and greed through a series of "money games".

Title: 47. The Cremator
Description: Set in Central Europe during World War II, a demented cremator believes cremation relieves earthly suffering and sets out to save the world.

Title: 48. The Good Guys and the Bad Guys
Description: Aging lawman Marshall Flagg and aging outlaw John McKay join forces when their respective positions in society are usurped by both a younger incompetent Marshal and young vicious gang leader Waco.

Title: 49. Pippi Longstocking
Description: Pippi Longstocking, a super-strong redheaded little girl, moves into her father's house Villa Villekulla, and has adventures with her next-door neighbors Tommy and Annika in this compilation film of the classic European TV series.

Title: 50. School for Unclaimed Girls
Description: A traumatized and troubled teenager is sent to an all-girls detention home where she strikes up an unlikely friendship with a fellow inmate.

Title: 51. Medea
Description: After his quest to retrieve the fabled Golden Fleece, Jason returns to Greece with powerful sorceress Medea. However, when the king banishes her, it's only human that Medea plots her furious revenge. Can they escape her wrath?

Title: 52. 99 Women
Description: A new female inmate at an island prison is abused by fellow convicts and staff, and her disillusionment with the new warden prompts her to join in an attempted breakout and mutiny.

Title: 53. Anne of the Thousand Days
Description: King Henry VIII of England discards one wife, Catharine of Aragon, who has failed to produce a male heir, in favor of the young and beautiful Anne Boleyn.

Title: 54. The Bridge at Remagen
Description: As the Allied armies close in, the Germans decide to blow up the last Rhine bridge, trapping their own men on the wrong side. But will it happen?

Title: 55. Marlowe
Description: A young woman from Kansas hires LA private detective Philip Marlowe to find her missing brother.

Title: 56. One on Top of the Other
Description: An unscrupulous doctor is accused of killing his asthmatic wife as part of an insurance scam, despite discovering that she has a doppelgänger who works as a stripper and call girl.

Title: 57. 100 Rifles
Description: In 1912 Mexico, a half-Yaqui bank robber seeking to buy guns for his people is pursued by an American lawman, but the pair soon team up with a beautiful revolutionary to fight off the Army.

Title: 58. The Sicilian Clan
Description: An ambitious young mobster plans an elaborate diamond heist while seducing the daughter of a ruthless mob patriarch as a determined police commissioner closes in on all of them.

Title: 59. Blue Movie
Description: Viva and Louis Waldon spend an idyllic afternoon together in an apartment in New York City.

Title: 60. The Undefeated
Description: After the Civil War, ex-Confederate soldiers heading for a new life in Mexico run into ex-Union cavalrymen selling horses to the Mexican government but they must join forces to fight off Mexican bandits and revolutionaries.

Title: 61. My Night at Maud's
Description: A devout Catholic man's rigid principles are challenged during a one-night stay with Maud, a divorced woman with an outsize personality.

Title: 62. Change of Habit
Description: As an incognito nun tries to help a doctor clean up an inner-city ghetto, the pair grow closer with time.

Title: 63. The Conspiracy of Torture
Description: In 16th century Italy, a young noblewoman plots with her lover and her family to murder her abusive father, leading to an uproar in the community and the Catholic Church.

Title: 64. The Laughing Woman
Description: A rich man with a penchant for degrading women subjects a female journalist to unpleasant S&M games, but, unbeknownst to him, she's the one who's manipulating him.

Title: 65. Shark
Description: A gunrunner loses his cargo near a small coastal Sudanese town so he's stuck there. When a woman hires him to raid a sunken ship in the shark-infested waters, he sees a chance to compensate for his losses. He's not the only one.

Title: 66. Hamlet
Description: Academy Award-winning director Tony Richardson brings Shakespeare's tragedy to the screen - with searing performances from Nicol Williamson as the melancholy Dane and future Academy Award-winner Anthony Hopkins as the deceitful Claudius.

Title: 67. The Rain People
Description: When a housewife finds out she is pregnant, she runs out of town looking for freedom to reevaluate her life decisions.

Title: 68. Love Camp 7
Description: Two female Army agents go undercover at a Nazi prison camp to get information from a scientist being held there.

Title: 69. Take the Money and Run
Description: The life and times of Virgil Starkwell, inept bank robber.

Title: 70. The Love Factor
Description: A race of sexy women from Angvia, a planet in another dimension, comes to Earth to kidnap women to repopulate their planet.

Title: 71. Model Shop
Description: George is unemployed, broke, about to be drafted to Vietnam, and suddenly madly in love with the divine Lola, a woman he has only briefly glimpsed. Now George searches for his potential amour through the City of Angels.

Title: 72. Goodbye, Mr. Chips
Description: This musical version of James Hilton's novel concerns shy, withdrawn English schoolteacher Arthur Chipping, who falls for flashy showgirl Katherine Bridges while teaching at Brookfield Boys' School outside London in the 1920's.

Title: 73. The Computer Wore Tennis Shoes
Description: At Medfield College, an accident with a donated computer gives Dexter Riley the ability to remember any knowledge learned instantly and perfectly.

Title: 74. The Curious Female
Description: In the distant future, the world is under the control of a master computer. However, small groups of people view ancient sex films, from the 20th Century, in secret for fun.

Title: 75. Attraction
Description: Married woman explores psychedelic English youth scene, engages in interracial affair with African-American man. Anti-Vietnam sentiments, violence, and sex depicted. Soundtrack by Freedom, offshoot of Procol Harum.

Title: 76. Horrors of Malformed Men
Description: After escaping from an insane asylum, a medical student assumes the identity of a mysterious dead man, who appeared to be his doppelganger, and gets lured to a sinister island ruled by a mad scientist and his malformed men.

Title: 77. Goodbye, Columbus
Description: An intelligent graduate and working-class Army veteran has an affair and clashes with a 'nouveau riche' young woman who cares not for birth control or the use of any other precautions to avoid pregnancy.

Title: 78. Camille 2000
Description: In Rome, a drug-addicted courtesan falls in love with a man who insists that she gives up her lavish, orgiastic lifestyle for fidelity, but tragedy soon ensures.

Title: 79. A Boy Named Charlie Brown
Description: Charlie Brown makes his way to the national spelling bee finals.

Title: 80. The House That Screamed
Description: A strict headmistress runs a secluded school for wayward girls in 19th century France, whose students are disappearing under mysterious circumstances.

Title: 81. Castle Keep
Description: During the Battle of the Bulge, an anachronistic count shelters a ragtag squad of Americans in his remote 10th Century castle hoping a battle there against the advancing Germans will not lead to its destruction and all the heritage within.

Title: 82. The Night of the Following Day
Description: Two men kidnap a girl off the streets, take her to a beach house owned by a drug-addicted stewardess, and hold her for ransom.

Title: 83. Top Sensation
Description: Hoping to sway her unbalanced son into losing his virginity, an oil baroness takes him and several of her decadent friends on a cruise, culminating in an orgy of lust and murder.

Title: 84. The April Fools
Description: A married man enters his boss' apartment to sign papers for a promotion and finds a party of 200 instead. He doesn't fit in, leaves with a woman, spends all night with her, falls in love with her--and finds out she's his boss' wife.

Title: 85. Crossplot
Description: An advertising executive sets out to find a woman for a new advertising campaign. His only clue to the woman is a photograph, and the search leads him into bewildering political ploys and mayhem.

Title: 86. The Trouble with Girls
Description: Chautauqua manager Walter Hale and his loyal business manager struggle to keep their traveling troupe together in small-town America.

Title: 87. Downhill Racer
Description: Quietly cocky David Chappellet joins the U.S. ski team as downhill racer and clashes with the team's coach, Eugene Claire.

Title: 88. The Girl from Rio
Description: Having established Femina, a secret city populated entirely by beautiful women, Sumuru plots to wage a war against all men.

Title: 89. A Thousand & One Nights
Description: Aldin, a vagabond water vendor, embarks on a series of fantastical and tragic misadventures through the Middle East in search of love, fortune, and power.

Title: 90. The Arrangement
Description: An adman attempts to rebuild his shattered life after suffering a nervous breakdown.

Title: 91. Sabata
Description: A master gunfighter sides with a banjo-playing drifter and a Mexican tramp to foil the dignitaries of Daugherty, who want to use stolen army money to buy land that the railroad will cross.

Title: 92. Baby Love
Description: Libidinous 15 year old English schoolgirl Lucy finds her single mother dead. They never had a good relationship, but this still unbalances her. She moves in with the family of her mother's old friend. She hates him and seduces his wife.

Title: 93. The Valley of Gwangi
Description: A cowboy named Tuck Kirby seeks fame and fortune by capturing an Allosaurus living in a Mexican valley and putting it in a wild west show. His star attraction, called the Gwangi, turns out to have an aversion to being shown in public.

Title: 94. The Oblong Box
Description: Aristocrat Julian Markham keeps his disfigured brother, Sir Edward, locked in a tower of his house. Sir Edward occasionally escapes and causes havoc around the town.

Title: 95. Burn!
Description: In 1844, a British mercenary helps the revolting slaves of an Antilles island colony gain independence from Portugal, but later returns to hunt down a local rebel leader and former protégé.

Title: 96. Putney Swope
Description: The board of directors at a Madison Avenue ad agency must elect a new chairman. In the maneuvering to make sure that enemies don't get votes, all the members accidentally cast their ballot for the board's token black man, Putney Swope.

Title: 97. Medium Cool
Description: A TV news reporter finds himself becoming personally involved in the violence that erupts around the 1968 Democratic National Convention.

Title: 98. Lions Love (... and Lies)
Description: Three actors in Hollywood live and love together. A director comes from New York to make a movie about actors and Hollywood.

Title: 99. The Illustrated Man
Description: In 1930s, a psychotic drifter who's after the mystery woman who covered his whole body in illustrations that foresee distant future shows three of them (The Veldt, The Long Rain and The Last Night of the World) to a mesmerized traveler.

Title: 100. Me, Natalie
Description: A young woman struggles for independence.
